.TH "pgste_perform_essa" 9 "pgste_perform_essa" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pgste_perform_essa \- perform ESSA actions on the PGSTE.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pgste_perform_essa
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long hva "  ","
.BI "int orc "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *oldpte "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *oldpgste "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
the memory context. It must have PGSTEs, no check is performed here!
.IP "hva" 12
the host virtual address of the page whose PGSTE is to be processed
.IP "orc" 12
the specific action to perform, see the ESSA_SET_* macros.
.IP "oldpte" 12
the PTE will be saved there if the pointer is not NULL.
.IP "oldpgste" 12
the old PGSTE will be saved there if the pointer is not NULL.
.SH "RETURN"
1 if the page is to be added to the CBRL, otherwise 0,
or < 0 in case of error. -EINVAL is returned for invalid values
of orc, -EFAULT for invalid addresses.
